e 80000 in aroa hv wnrk aiiww stoppages and shutdowns was a spreading strike in the oil indus try by the Oil Workers Union CIO and a curtailment of elec trical equipment to three divisions of General Motors Corporation William S Bullock general man ager of Detroits municipally own ed public transportation system said only a four days supply of gasoline remained for the citys approximately 1400 buses in daily operation The oil strike began with a stop page by truckers later spread to workers in the Socony Vacuum Company plant in suburban Tren ton and was reported affecting nearby"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-12T17:38:26.237Z", "group": ["ndnp/ncu", "university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78002169/1945-09-20/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lily_ver01:data:sn78002169:00279558868:1945092001:0225/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=430&w=324", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lily_ver01:data:sn78002169:00279558868:1945092001:0225/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=860&w=649", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lily_ver01/data/sn78002169/00279558868/1945092001/0225.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new hanover", "united states", "new hanover county", "wilmington", "north carolina"], "location_city": ["wilmington"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["new hanover"], "location_state": ["north carolina"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["9", "0", "5", "8", "sn78002169", "7", "0000000001", "6", "2", "1"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn78002169"], "number_page": ["0000000001"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "2", "7", "9", "5", "5", "8", "8", "6", "8"], "onl